            <abstract xml:lang="en">
              <p>This paper presents a framework for modelling legislative deliberation in the form of dialogues. Roughly, in legislative dialogues coalitions can dynamically change and propose rule-based theories associated with different utility functions, depending on the legislative theory the coalitions are trying to determine. CCS CONCEPTS • Applied computing → Law, social and behavioral sciences; Law.</p>
